###
# SipSafe API Tests
# Use with VS Code REST Client extension or import to Postman
###

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001
@sessionId = 1

### 1. Start a Session
# POST /api/session/start
# Creates a new drinking session (or returns existing active session)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/session/start
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 2. Get Session by ID
# GET /api/session/[id]
# Retrieves session details with all drinks
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/session/{{sessionId}}

###

### 3. End Session
# POST /api/session/end
# Ends the current active session
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/session/end
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 4. Log a Drink (Beer)
# POST /api/drink
# Adds a drink to the active session
# Note: volumeOz is camelCase, duration is ISO interval format
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/drink
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "beer",
  "volumeOz": 12,
  "duration": "30 minutes"
}

###

### 5. Log a Wine Drink
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/drink
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "wine",
  "volumeOz": 8,
  "duration": "45 minutes"
}

###

### 6. Log a Shot
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/drink
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "whiskey_shot",
  "volumeOz": 1.5,
  "duration": "5 minutes"
}

###

### 7. Get Resources
# GET /api/resources
# Returns safety resources
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/resources

###

